news.title: LEDs to replace 54,000 sodium-based street lights in Greater Noida
news.para: ​The Greater Noida Industrial Development Authority (GNIDA) had floated a tender for replacement of the 54,000 high-pressure sodium bulbs on street lights and private firm Surya Roshni has won the contract for the project, the officials said.

news.title: Pune civic body eyes arbitration to end legal battles, mop up revenue
news.para: The Pune Municipal Corporation (PMC) has taken up 10 cases of property tax disputes, pending in courts for 8-10 years, for disposing of through arbitration and generate Rs35-crore revenue.

news.title: Nagpur: HC takes up issue of public lands being encroached, regularized
news.para: Pointing out various orders passed by the HC, the bench said all those broadly point towards illegalities of grave nature committed by Nagpur Municipal Corporation (NMC) and Nagpur Improvement Trust (NIT) officials.

news.title: Nashik: Tehsildars get powers to issue NA permits to identified land parcels
news.para: Nashik district collector Suraj Mandhare said, “We are now granting these rights to tehsildars to provide the NA permits to land parcels that have already been marked as residential areas in the development plan.”

news.title: Gurugram civic body earmarks two more sites to dump construction waste
news.para: The MCG has taken five acres of land on lease in Basai and will also make use of nine acres of its land in Baliawas village for the disposal of C&D waste.

news.title: HomeLane raises Rs 371 crore in series-E funding
news.para: With the current round of funding, HomeLane has raised more than Rs 765 crore ($104 million) in funds over the last seven years. The new funding will help the company accelerate its growth, with revenue targets of Rs 2,500 crore by FY24.

news.title: Ghaziabad: Six years on, not a single unit delivered under PMAY
news.para: In fact, of the 10,850 units sanctioned in the city, the Ghaziabad Development Authority (GDA) is supposed to construct some 3,496 units. However, only 240 have been constructed under the Madhuban Bapudham housing scheme to date.

news.title: Reserve price of properties to be cut: Chandigarh housing board
news.para: In the meeting ,which was held under the chairmanship of UT adviser Dharam Pal, who is also the chairman of the CHB, it was decided to reduce reserve price of commercial units on leasehold basis by 20% and residential units on leasehold basis by 10%. In the next e-tenders, the reserve price will be kept after reduction.

news.title: Chennai: 770 buildings under scanner over solar panel rules violation
news.para: While the Tamil Nadu Combined Development and Building Rules mandate these panels for constructions receiving completion certificate from the CMDA, several buildings have failed to install the devices.

news.title: Rajasthan housing department makes it mandatory for big plots to recycle wastewater
news.para: The Urban Development and Housing (UDH) department has issued an order after making it a mandatory provision in the building bylaws. Provision is not meant for wastewater from toilets.

news.title: Lodha ties-up with Tata Power for EV charging stations across all projects
news.para: Under this partnership, Tata Power will install EV Charging stations at Lodha developments across MMR and Pune. These chargers will be accessible to all Lodha residents and visitors who are EV owners.

news.title: Hope to pay about Rs 551 crore debt like last year: N Srinivasan, Chairman, India Cements
news.para: ​​"Last year, the company repaid Rs 551 crore debt, which is quite substantial. This year, it hopes to repay an equal amount depending on the impact of the Covid-19 pandemic," he said while addressing shareholders at the 75th AGM held through virtual platform.

news.title: Greater Noida: Soon, you can get 'no dues' certificates for properties online
news.para: The software, developed by Tech Mahindra, is akin to a net-banking facility and would allow allottees to obtain no-due certificate online on submission of necessary documents with just a couple of mouse clicks, they said.

news.title: Maharashtra cabinet clears proposal of redeveloping MHADA colonies in Mumbai
news.para: ​​The cabinet also cleared a proposal of redeveloping MHADA (Maharashtra Housing & Area Development Authority) colonies in Motilal Nagar in suburban Goregaon where 5,300 houses are located at the present.

news.title: Ahmedabad: I-T department conducts searches at premises of Sambhaav Group
news.para: The searches, which were initiated around 6 am in different parts of the city, are expected to continue for a couple of more days, he said, adding that the searches are being conducted to detect tax evasion, if any.
